<span id="freeTextContainer1870953429010046186">4.5 stars. Fresh, original fantasy using the United States of the 19th century as its backdrop. This creation of a truly &quot;American&quot; fantasy novel was truly original and I thought made it a cut above a lot of cookie cutter fantasy stories. <br/><br/>Winner: Locus Award for Best Fantasy Novel (1988)<br/>Winner: Mythopoeic Fantasy Award for Adult Literature (1988)<br/>Nominee: Hugo Award for Best Novel (1988)<br/>Nominee: World Fantasy Award for Best Novel (1988) </span>
  <span id="freeText1870953429010046186" style="display:none">4.5 stars. Fresh, original fantasy using the United States of the 19th century as its backdrop. This creation of a truly "American" fantasy novel was truly original and I thought made it a cut above a lot of cookie cutter fantasy stories. <br /><br />Winner: Locus Award for Best Fantasy Novel (1988)<br />Winner: Mythopoeic Fantasy Award for Adult Literature (1988)<br />Nominee: Hugo Award for Best Novel (1988)<br />Nominee: World Fantasy Award for Best Novel (1988) </span>
