<div id="review_13801871" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/13801871" />
    <a title="Radu Stanculescu" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/748293-radu-stanculescu"><img alt="Radu Stanculescu" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1432030977p2/748293.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/13801871?book_show_action=true">Jan 28, 2008</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Radu Stanculescu" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Radu Stanculescu" href="/user/show/748293-radu-stanculescu">Radu Stanculescu</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/748293-radu-stanculescu?shelf=alternate-history">alternate-history</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/748293-radu-stanculescu?shelf=locus-award">locus-award</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/748293-radu-stanculescu?shelf=fantasy">fantasy</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer13801871" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13702451010335671574">The &quot;Alvin Maker&quot; series was my second contact with O.S. Card after the &quot;Ender&quot; series, and I&apos;m delighted to say it&apos;s different and it&apos;s still good. :) It was an interesting mix of history, religion, magic and insights into human morals and what motivates our actions. The magic is treated very &quot;practically&quot;, like an extra talent that you need to work on to develop, and thankfully it doesn&apos;t take over the book while still being an important part of it. The one negative thing is that I didn&apos;t get </span>
  <span id="freeText13702451010335671574" style="display:none">The "Alvin Maker" series was my second contact with O.S. Card after the "Ender" series, and I'm delighted to say it's different and it's still good. :) It was an interesting mix of history, religion, magic and insights into human morals and what motivates our actions. The magic is treated very "practically", like an extra talent that you need to work on to develop, and thankfully it doesn't take over the book while still being an important part of it. The one negative thing is that I didn't get into the main character's skin like I did in the "Ender" series, but not because the characterization isn't good (it's actually one of the strongest points of Card's work). I'm not exactly sure why, I'll have to reread it (or at least look over it again) to find the reasons. I'd give it 3.5 stars for that, verging on 4.</span>
  <a data-text-id="13702451010335671574" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


